-- UN Green Climate Fund Signs Agreement to Set Up HQ in S. Korea
-- B y   H e e s u   L e e
-- 2013-06-10T08:07:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-10/un-green-climate-fund-signs-agreement-to-set-up-hq-in-s-korea.html
The United Nations Green Climate
Fund signed an agreement with  South Korea  to locate its
headquarters in Incheon, west of Seoul.  The fund chose South Korea from six bidders last year,
according to a  statement  on the fund’s website. The agreement
includes privileges for the fund’s staff, Sung Moon Up, deputy
director general at South Korea’s Ministry of  Foreign Affairs ,
said by phone today, without giving details.  The UN fund plans to raise $100 billion by 2020 to help
countries curb greenhouse gas emissions, Sung said. Today’s
agreement is subject to parliamentary approval.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Heesu Lee in Seoul at 
